[src:open-redirect-defense/http-302] This may be due to the user not having permission to a resource or needing an account of some sort, or attempting a prohibited action (e.g. creating a duplicate record where only one is allowed).
[src:open-redirect-defense/http-302] This code is also typically used if the request provided authentication by answering the WWW-Authenticate header field challenge, but the server did not accept that authentication.
